---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <title>Academics &ndash; Nolan Welch</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Learn about Nolan Welch's academic work in linguistics, computational semantics, and research-driven software infrastructure."
    />
  </Fragment>

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6">Academics</h1>

    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-6">
      I&rsquo;m a double major in Computer Science and Hispanic Linguistics at
      <a
        href="https://www.unc.edu"
        class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >
        UNC-Chapel Hill</a
      >, graduating in Spring 2025. My academic work explores the intersection
      of language, logic, and system design.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-4">Current Research</h2>
    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
      My senior honors thesis explores how code-switching reflects emotional
      valence in mixed-language discourse. I&rsquo;m interested in whether
      sociolinguistic patterns can inform sentiment analysis systems in ways
      traditional models miss.
    </p>
    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-6">
      I approach this work through both formal semantic analysis and pragmatic
      framing, combining annotated corpora, syntactic typology, and natural
      language inference tools.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-4">Broader Interests</h2>
    <ul
      class="list-disc list-inside text-lg text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-6 space-y-2"
    >
      <li>Computational semantics and mixed-code sentiment analysis</li>
      <li>Event structure and argument realization</li>
      <li>Human-in-the-loop reasoning systems</li>
      <li>The limits of language as a vehicle for meaning</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-4">Honors & Coursework</h2>
    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
      Honors Carolina Scholar &middot; Spanish Department Honors Thesis &middot;
      Graduate-level coursework in syntax, semantics, and computational
      linguistics.
    </p>
    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-6">
      Recipient of the Sterling A. Stoudemire Prize for Excellence in Spanish
      and the Larry King Award for the Study of Minority Languages in the
      Iberian Peninsula.
    </p>

    <a href="/" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 underline"
      >&larr; Back home</a
    >
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
